description:
## Bug

In desktop/src-tauri/src/lib.rs connect_relay(), the receive loop is:

    tokio::spawn(async move {
        let mut rx = conn.rx;
        loop {
            let Some(event) = rx.recv().await else { break };
            match event {
                ClientEvent::Reconnecting { delay_secs } => { /* log + emit status */ }
                ClientEvent::Disconnected => {
                    tracing::error!("relay disconnected");
                    break;
                }
                _ => {}
            }
        }
        let _ = app.emit("nie://status", "Disconnected.");
    });

When the underlying transport connection drops, the event loop receives Disconnected and breaks, terminating the loop permanently. The Tauri frontend receives 'Disconnected.' but there is no mechanism to reconnect — the tx channel stored in RelayState remains stale (pointing at the dead connection), and any subsequent send_chat() call will return a channel-closed error.

Contrast with the TUI, which handles Reconnecting/Reconnected events and republishes HPKE keys on reconnect.

## Impact

Any relay connection drop (network hiccup, relay restart) permanently disconnects the desktop app. The user must restart the app to reconnect.

## Fix

On Disconnected, call connect_with_retry again and update the RelayState.tx with the new channel. Handle the Reconnected event to republish the HPKE key and key package.
